e, C.H., Pershing, A.J., Climate drives sea change (2007) Science, 315, pp. 1084-1085; Gudjonsson, S., Einarsson, S.M., Antonsson, T., Gudbergsson, G., Relation of grilse to salmon ratio to environmental changes in several wild stocks of Atlantic salmon (Salmo salar) in Iceland (1995) Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 52, pp. 1385-1398; Hannesson, R., Geographical distribution of fish catches and temperature variations in the northeast Atlantic since 1945 (2007) Marine Policy, 31, pp. 32-39; Hurrell, J.W., Decadal Trends in the North Atlantic Oscillation: regional temperatures and precipitation (1995) Science, 269, pp. 676-679; Hutchings, J.A., Myers, R.A., The evolution of alternative mating strategies in variable environments (1994) Evolution Ecology, 8, pp. 256-268; Jaroensutasinee, M., Jaroensutansinee, K., Bubble nest habitat characteristics of wild siamese fighting fish (2001) Journal of Fish Biology, 58, pp. 1311-1319; Jones, M.W., Hutchings, J.A., The influence of male parr body size and mate competition on fertilization success and effective population size in Atlantic salmon (2001) Heredity, 86, pp. 675-684; Jones, P.D., Osborn, T.J., Briffa, K.R., The evolution of climate over the last millennium (2001) Science, 292, pp. 662-667; Jonsson, N., Jonsson, B., Size and age of maturity of Atlantic salmon correlate with the North Atlantic Oscillation Index (NAOI) (2004) Journal of Fish Biology, 64, pp. 241-247; Jonsson, B., Jonsson, N., Factors affecting marine production of Atlantic salmon (Salmo salar) (2004) Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 61, pp. 2369-2383; Juanes, J., Perez, E., Garcia-Vazquez, E., Reproductive strategies in small populations: using Atlantic salmon as a case study (2007) Ecology of Freshwater Fish, 16, pp. 468-475; Lehodey, P., Alheit, J., Barange, M., Climate variability, fish, and fisheries (2006) Journal of Climate, 19, pp. 5009-5030; Lessios, H.A., Kessing, B.D., Robertson, D.R., Massive gene flow a